metadata.name: The Edge of Meaning #14
metadata.description:
Where sight ends, there is meaning, maybe. But maybe not something that we can understand. And maybe not something we can see.

AKA a couple of fragment shaders and a vertex shader roll terrain and reveal a message. The typeface is custom built for this series.

Press [spacebar] to toggle play/pause.

When paused, press [p] to create hi-res PNG.

metadata.name: ____ - Iteration 1 #63
metadata.description:
This project is part of a larger experiment that explores and celebrates the process of making generative art by progressively releasing iterations, working towards a final release on my main account (tz1RkYY3jr1ocuPdQqrRefr5FqoawKQsmBmD). The iterations will be titled ____ 0.1, ____ 0.2, etc. At this point, the number of iterations has not been determined, but more information will be provided as this experiment unfolds.

The final release will only be made available to those who have collected each iteration (using an allowlist), and will be released for free.

metadata.name: GEN XYZ Das Occult #4738
metadata.description:
A 10k Generative Profile Pic collection
GEN XYZ Das Occult - by culla - @tamccullough

move over cryptopunks
there is a new group on the scene

100% code - not an image composition

A bunch of common palettes
A selection of rare palettes
And a smaller set of ultra rare palettes
However, rarity will be based on what combinations the code produces

The majority of tokens will not have a special trait
However your token might have one or even multiple special traits
But, be aware that only the last special trait added will be listed in the features

Even then, look closely, because not all aspects of the canvas are included in the features. Collectors should still look closely and choose what they like when buying on secondary.

Which team are you on? X or O?

Thank you for supporting an emerging artist in the generative art space

1x for each Inkspunk, TwoFourQunk, V0iD, DeeManz, Punkasso and CR0$$KULL
You would have needed to transfer the above tokens to your mint wallet at the time of the snapshot

metadata.name: September #17
metadata.description:
The Summer Ends
---------------
Controls:
S or double tap (mobile): Download image

A: Toggle loading animation (off by default to improve performance)

1-6: Modify scale (1 = default, 1500 x 2000px, 6 = maximum, 9000 x 12000px (performance intensive, will take a long time to render))
F: Fit to current screen size

T: Toggle grain and texture overlay
H: Toggle shape outlines

B: Cycle border sizes (0 -> 50 -> 75 -> 100 -> 150px)
C: Cycle border colors

I: Cycle visible layers

L: Toggle “live mode”. This mode will continuously redraw a new output every few seconds using the same base parameters as the original output, but with slight variations.

You can modify the x and y url parameters to set a custom size. Note that the image will change to fit the new size, but overall drawing style, colors, etc. will remain the same.
(For example, for a 1000x2000 image, add &x=1000&y=2000)

metadata.name: PixelDeMNs - Series V #42
metadata.description:
** Prerendered Images w/ randomized Layers

PixelDeMNs Series V

All PixelDeMNs spawn DeMN Tokens weekly. Your DeMN Token earnings will automatically be transferred to your PixelDeMN holding wallet every week. PixelDeMN owners have been receiving DeMN Token drops since December 2021.
 
Series V DeMN Tokens apply a modifier to all of your PixelDeMNs owned and are stackable. For example, if you own 5 PixelDeMNs you would normally receive 105 DeMN Tokens per week. If you generate a 5% modifier PixelDeMN, you will receive 126 Tokens plus a 5% bonus. If you get another 2% PixelDeMN, you will receive 147 Tokens and a 7% bonus.

See your PixelDeMN Stats at PixelDeMNs.xyz

Join the #DeMNHorde
Twitter @NatasToken
natastoken.xyz

metadata.name: Psilocybe Azurescens #49
metadata.description:
Psilocybe Azurescens is a generative algorithm that draws a very potent psychedelic fungus. The Azurescens species occurs naturally along a small area of the West Coast of the United States, including in parts of Oregon and California.  The mushroom has an affinity for coastal dune grasses.

The halftone hatching patterns and 3d mushroom geometries are all unique and driven by fx features and the transaction hash.  

- Double click to enable turntable mode
- Click or touch and drag to rotate in 3D, scroll or pinch to zoom
- Don’t eat too many of these super funky boomerangs off-chain - they are strong!

Created by @capnganj - one love <3
